<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,350,583]" box="[160,276,350,374]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,350,374]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,350,583]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">
<emphasis box="[160,551,385,410]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1835" box="[160,397,385,410]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scatonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbatus">Scatonomus barbatus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Valois &amp; Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Silva, 2020" authorityName="Valois &amp; Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Silva" authorityYear="2020" box="[408,551,385,410]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scatonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canhedoae" status="sp. nov.">S. canhedoae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[557,645,385,410]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Erichson" authorityYear="1835" box="[653,803,385,410]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scatonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciculatus">
<emphasis box="[653,803,385,410]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">S. fasciculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vulcano and Pereira" authorityYear="1973" box="[858,1032,385,410]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scatonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulosawayai">
<emphasis box="[858,1032,385,410]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">S. paulosawayai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have deep lateral emarginations filled with setae at the clypeal edge (
<figureCitation box="[814,905,419,444]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1294,1317]" captionTargetBox="[171,1141,146,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-89@7.[163,1153,142,1262]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Head, dorsal view. (a) Scatonomus barbatus stat. rev.; (b) S. canhedoae sp. nov. (holotype); (c) S. chalybaeus; (d) S. fasciculatus; (e) S. foresti sp. nov. (holotype); (f) S. insignis; (g) S. janssensi; (h) S. mitzae sp. nov. (holotype); (i) S. paulosawayai (holotype); (j, k) S. thalassinus; (l) S. viridis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020909/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(a, b, d, i)). However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vulcano and Pereira" authorityYear="1973" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scatonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulosawayai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">S. paulosawayai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the clypeal edge lacking median teeth and the median portion between the lateral emarginations with rectangular shape (
<figureCitation box="[721,816,489,514]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1294,1317]" captionTargetBox="[171,1141,146,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-89@7.[163,1153,142,1262]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Head, dorsal view. (a) Scatonomus barbatus stat. rev.; (b) S. canhedoae sp. nov. (holotype); (c) S. chalybaeus; (d) S. fasciculatus; (e) S. foresti sp. nov. (holotype); (f) S. insignis; (g) S. janssensi; (h) S. mitzae sp. nov. (holotype); (i) S. paulosawayai (holotype); (j, k) S. thalassinus; (l) S. viridis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020909/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(i)), dorsum with green or blue reflections (
<figureCitation box="[291,381,523,548]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1145,1168]" captionTargetBox="[194,1153,143,1113]" captionTargetId="figure-187@5.[163,1153,142,1113]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Dorsal habitus. (a) S Scatonomus barbatus stat. rev.; (b) S. canhedoae sp. nov.; (holotype); (c) S. chalybaeus; (d) S. fasciculatus; (e) S. foresti sp. nov. (holotype); (f) S. insignis; (g) S. janssensi; (h) S. mitzae sp. nov. (holotype); (i) S. paulosawayai (holotype); (j, k) S. thalassinus; (l) S. viridis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020905/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(i)), head and pronotum wrinkled and elytral interstriae opaque, with well-defined microgranulation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="1105" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,643,1362]" box="[160,320,643,667]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,320,643,667]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Redescription</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,643,1362]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,218,678,703]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Male</emphasis>
: unknown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[354,441,678,703]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Female</emphasis>
: length: 
<quantity box="[544,628,678,703]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
. Dorsum with black, green or blue reflections (
<figureCitation box="[168,257,713,738]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1145,1168]" captionTargetBox="[194,1153,143,1113]" captionTargetId="figure-187@5.[163,1153,142,1113]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Dorsal habitus. (a) S Scatonomus barbatus stat. rev.; (b) S. canhedoae sp. nov.; (holotype); (c) S. chalybaeus; (d) S. fasciculatus; (e) S. foresti sp. nov. (holotype); (f) S. insignis; (g) S. janssensi; (h) S. mitzae sp. nov. (holotype); (i) S. paulosawayai (holotype); (j, k) S. thalassinus; (l) S. viridis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020905/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(i)). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[301,363,713,738]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Head</emphasis>
: surface wrinkled (
<figureCitation box="[573,668,713,738]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1294,1317]" captionTargetBox="[171,1141,146,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-89@7.[163,1153,142,1262]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Head, dorsal view. (a) Scatonomus barbatus stat. rev.; (b) S. canhedoae sp. nov. (holotype); (c) S. chalybaeus; (d) S. fasciculatus; (e) S. foresti sp. nov. (holotype); (f) S. insignis; (g) S. janssensi; (h) S. mitzae sp. nov. (holotype); (i) S. paulosawayai (holotype); (j, k) S. thalassinus; (l) S. viridis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020909/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(i)). Clypeo-genal and fronto-clypeal sutures wide, sulcate. Anterior clypeal and genal edges with rows of ventral, orange setae (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1294,1317]" captionTargetBox="[171,1141,146,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-89@7.[163,1153,142,1262]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Head, dorsal view. (a) Scatonomus barbatus stat. rev.; (b) S. canhedoae sp. nov. (holotype); (c) S. chalybaeus; (d) S. fasciculatus; (e) S. foresti sp. nov. (holotype); (f) S. insignis; (g) S. janssensi; (h) S. mitzae sp. nov. (holotype); (i) S. paulosawayai (holotype); (j, k) S. thalassinus; (l) S. viridis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020909/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(i)). Antennal club filled with short setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[635,719,782,807]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Thorax</emphasis>
: pronotal surface wrinkled and puncticulate. Pronotal disc slightly elevated at the anteromedian portion. Mid-longitudinal sulcus on pronotal disc filled with fine punctures. Transverse carina of hypomera complete, reaching the lateral edge. Anterior and lateral edges of hypomera densely coated with setae. Surface of mesepimeron and mesanepisternum with green reflections, finely striate. Disc of metaventrite flat, punctate, with shallow longitudinal sulcus medially. Lateral lobes of metaventrite with well-defined microgranulation and sparse shallow punctures. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[285,355,1025,1050]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Elytra</emphasis>
: striae thin, punctures shallowly impressed. Seventh stria almost reaching the elytral base. Eighth stria absent at anterior one-fifth. Ninth stria carinate, inconspicuous near basal portion of elytra. Interstriae punctate, with well-defined microgranulation. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[369,631,1129,1154]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Legs [ventral surface]</emphasis>
: profemora puncticulate, posterior edge with setose punctures near trochanter. Outer edge of protibiae with two acute teeth, apical tooth longer than median and basal teeth. Meso- and metafemora finely punctate. Outer carina of mesotibiae and metatibiae with row of small teeth. Inner edge of mesotibiae and metatibiae carinate, except by its apical one-third. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[717,834,1267,1292]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Abdomen</emphasis>
: posterior half of ventrites II– IV slightly depressed. Ventrite V 3 times shorter than ventrite VI. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[914,1028,1302,1327]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1105">Pygidium</emphasis>
: shiny and puncticulate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
